Dates are between May 2013 and May 2015

theData <- read.csv('KBP-2013-14-15-FULL-DFE.csv')

# Data Cleaning
# Getting dates in the correct format
theData$Date.of.Death <- sub("\\/20", "/", theData$Date.of.Death)
theData$Date.of.Death <- sub(" ", "", theData$Date.of.Death)
theData$Date.of.Death <- as.Date(theData$Date.of.Death, "%d/%m/%y")

Subsetting Some of the Data

# By race
black  <- subset(theData, Race == "Black")
white  <- subset(theData, Race == "White")
latino <- subset(theData, Race == "Latino")

# Shooting subset
black <- subset(black, Cause.of.Death = "Shooting")
white <- subset(white, Cause.of.Death = "Shooting")
latino <- subset(latino, Cause.of.Death = "Shooting")

Deaths involving police officers by state

library(ggplot2)
shootings <- subset(theData, Cause.of.Death = "Shooting")
statesums <- table(shootings$State)
statef <- as.data.frame(statesums)
colnames(statef) <- c("state.of.res", "count")

statef <- transform(statef,
                    state.of.res=reorder(state.of.res,count))

ggplot(statef) + geom_bar(aes(x = state.of.res, y = count),
                          stat="identity",
                          fill = "gray") +
                          coord_flip() + theme(axis.text.y=element_text(size=rel(0.8)))+ 
                          labs(title = "Officer Involved Deaths by State")

Deaths by Police Officer by City

citysums <- table(theData$City)
cityf <- as.data.frame(citysums)
colnames(cityf) <- c("city.of.res", "count")

cityf <- transform(cityf,
                    city.of.res=reorder(city.of.res,count))

cityf <- subset(cityf, count > 7 & count < 50)

ggplot(cityf) + geom_bar(aes(x = city.of.res, y = count),
                          stat="identity",
                          fill = "gray") +
                          coord_flip() + theme(axis.text.y=element_text(size=rel(1)))+ 
                          labs(title = "Officer Involved Deaths by City")

theDataArmed <- subset(theData, theData$Was.the.deceased.armed. != "Unknown")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Was.the.deceased.armed. != "Disputed")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Was.the.deceased.armed. != "Unclear")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Was.the.deceased.armed. != "<NA>")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Was.the.deceased.armed. != "")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Asian")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Other")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Pacific Islander")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Native American")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Unknown")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "")
theDataArmed <- subset(theDataArmed, theDataArmed$Race != "Latino")


ggplot(theDataArmed) + geom_bar(aes(x = Race, fill = Was.the.deceased.armed.),

                           theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +

Armed v. Unarmed over Time Black

We see an increase in unarmed fatalities

blackData$Armed <- ifelse(blackData$Was.the.deceased.armed. == "Yes", 0, 1)
whiteData$Armed <- ifelse(whiteData$Was.the.deceased.armed. == "Yes", 0, 1)

Armed v. Unarmed over Time

ggplot(whiteData, aes(x=Date.of.Death, y = Armed)) +
  geom_point(position=position_jitter(w=0.05, h=0.05)) +
  geom_smooth() +
  labs(ylab("1 = Unarmed, 0 = Armed")) +
  ggtitle("White Proportion of Deaths Armed/Unarmed Over Time") +
  xlab("Date of Death")

ggplot(blackData, aes(x=Date.of.Death, y = Armed)) +
